arts.ttl: Erling Haaland smashes 90-year goalscoring record with brace in Norway win
arts.sum: Erling Haaland becomes the highest scorer in the history of the Norway men's national team with a brace in their 3-0 UEFA Nations League win over Slovenia.

arts.ttl: Erling Haaland becomes Norway’s all-time record goalscorer in just his 36th international match
arts.sum: The Man City striker has 34 goals - the previous record was set 90 years ago

arts.ttl: Haaland becomes Norway’s all-time top scorer
arts.sum: Juves scored 33 goals for Norway’s men’s team in 41 appearances between March 1928 and June 1937, his final goal for the national team was in June 1934, precisely at the Ullevaal - the same stadium where Haaland would take his record 90 years later. The Man City striker’s second goal took him past Juves to claim the record outright.

arts.ttl: City's Haaland sets Norway scoring record in win
arts.sum: Erling Haaland marked his first game as Norway captain by becoming his country's all-time leading scorer on Thursday.
